                    },
                    {
                        "type": "rich_text_section",
                        "elements": [
                            {
                                "type": "text",
                                "text": "\n\nI don't think we want to gatekeep it already in "
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "text",
                                "text": "makeCluster()",
                                "style": {
                                    "code": true
                                }
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "text",
                                "text": ", because we\ncannot predict what additional cluster "
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "text",
                                "text": "type",
                                "style": {
                                    "code": true
                                }
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "text",
                                "text": ":s exist out there, or will be\nadded in the future. There might be valid cases where the specification are not\nthe common ones that we already know of.\n\nI suspect this is the reason for why argument "
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "text",
                                "text": "spec",
                                "style": {
                                    "code": true
                                }
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "text",
                                "text": " is documented in very\nbroad terms;\n\n    spec: A specification appropriate to the type of cluster.\n\nInstead, I think it should be up to each cluster type to check for valid "
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "text",
                                "text": "spec",
                                "style": {
                                    "code": true
                                }
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "text",
                                "text": "\nand "
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "text",
                                "text": "...",
                                "style": {
                                    "code": true
                                }
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "text",
                                "text": " input, e.g. "
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "text",
                                "text": "parallel::makePSOCKcluster()",
                                "style": {
                                    "code": true
                                }
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "text",
                                "text": " and\n"
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "text",
                                "text": "parallel::makeForkCluster()",
                                "style": {
                                    "code": true
                                }
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "text",
                                "text": ".  So, in this case it's\n"
