        "text": "*[Bug 18364] Initializing Column Improper Length*\n<https:\/\/bugs.r-project.org\/show_bug.cgi?id=18364>\n\n--- Comment #6 from Suharto Anggono (<mailto:suharto_anggono@yahoo.com|suharto_anggono@yahoo.com>) ---\nNote that\n\n    df$c[3:4] = 9:10\n\nis equivalent to\n\n    `*tmp*` &lt;- df\n    df &lt;- \"$&lt;-\"(`*tmp*`, c, value=\"[&lt;-\"(\"$\"(`*tmp*`, c), 3:4, value=9:10))\n    rm(`*tmp*`)\n\n.\n\nIt has the same effect as\n\n    tmp = df$c\n    tmp[3:4] = 9:10\n    df$c = tmp\n\n.\n\nWith initially\n\n    df = data.frame(a = 1:4, b = 5:8)\n\n,\n\n    tmp = df$c # NULL\n    tmp[3:4] = 9:10 # tmp has length 4, NA at 1,2\n    df$c = tmp\n\n.",
